FRANCE DAYBOOK: Lagarde Visits Brazil to Seek IMF Bid Support

-- B y  
-- 
2011-05-30T04:06:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/france-daybook-lagarde-visits-brazil-to-seek-imf-bid-support.html
French Finance Minister Christine
Lagarde is in  Brazil  today as part of an effort to broaden
support in developing countries for her candidacy to head the
 International Monetary Fund . Brazil was the first emerging-
market country to invite her after she announced her candidacy.
She also plans to visit China, India and countries in Africa
and the  Middle East , she said yesterday.  ALL TIMES CET  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Accor SA holds its annual general meeting. (10:00 a.m.,
Paris)
* Wendel SA holds its shareholders meeting. (3:30 p.m., Paris)  GOVERNMENT:
* President Nicolas Sarkozy meets with Luxembourg Prime
Minister Jean-Claude Juncker at Elysees
* Prime Minister Francois Fillon visits hospital and cancer
research center in Selestat and Strasbourg.
* Finance Minister  Christine Lagarde  visits Brazil concerning
her IMF candidacy.
* Transportation Minister Nathalie Kosciusko-Morizet leads
round table on rail freight at 10:45 a.m.
* Agriculture Minister Bruno Le Maire meets with regional
representatives about drought in Seine-et-Marne at 3 p.m.
* Budget Minister Francois Baroin meets with inter-ministerial
delegate for economic intelligence Olivier Buquen at 5 p.m.
*Industry Minister Eric Besson meets with Cegid CEO Patrick
Bertrand at 5 p.m.  EQUITIES:
* Carrefour SA (CA)  : The world’s second-largest retailer was
contacted by Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de
Acucar Chairman Abilio Diniz in recent weeks to discuss ways to
combine Carrefour’s Brazilian stores with Pao de Acucar’s
network, the Wall Street Journal said yesterday, citing
unidentified people familiar with the matter. Shares gained 0.3
percent to 30.34 euros.
* LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA (MC)  : The world’s
biggest luxury-goods maker’s acquisition of Bulgari SpA will
allow LVMH to double its hard-luxury division turnover, Borsa &
Finanza reported May 28, citing Bulgari Chief Executive Officer
Francesco Trapani. Shares rose 1.6 percent to 118.35 euros.
* Total SA (FP)  : Europe’s third-biggest oil company acquired
a 25 percent stake in a Qatari offshore hydrocarbon exploration
license, state-run  Qatar Petroleum  said yesterday in an e-
mailed press release. Cnooc Ltd, awarded the license to explore
and develop the field in 2009, will retain a 75 percent stake,
Qatar Petroleum said. Shares rose 0.9 percent to 39.54 euros.  MARKETS:
*The CAC 40 Index rose 33.76, or 0.9 percent, to 3,950.98
*The broader SBF 120 Index rose 0.8 percent to 2,979.43 points.  INTERVIEWS ELSEWHERE:
